The paper proposes a method that uses deep-pose regression neural networks for automatic registration between cone-beam CT images and scanned dental models. This involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are all relevant to the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
